---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About — Clawed-Code" description="Why Clawed-Code exists.">
  <article class="prose-claw mx-auto max-w-2xl pt-10">
    <h1>About Clawed-Code</h1>
    <p>
      Clawed-Code is a field notebook for working with Claude and other coding
      agents. I put the lessons somewhere other people can find them rather
      than let them rot in a private notes app.
    </p>
    <p>
      Everything here is written from practice. If a guide is on the site,
      I've used it on real code. If a prompt is listed, it has earned its
      keep. If a tool is featured, I use it every day.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial bias</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Smaller is better.</strong> Short prompts, small tools, tight feedback loops.</li>
      <li><strong>Taste beats hype.</strong> "This model changed everything" posts age badly. Workflows age well.</li>
      <li><strong>Readable code over magic.</strong> Agents write better code when the surrounding codebase is legible.</li>
      <li><strong>Measure the thing.</strong> Cost, tokens, latency, diffs — numbers beat vibes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who runs this</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/amirhjalali">Amir Jalali</a>. I also maintain
      <a href="https://github.com/amirhjalali/monclaude">monclaude</a>, a status
      line for Claude Code.
    </p>

    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <p>
      This is an open repository. Guides, prompts, and tools can all be added
      via PR — see the <a href="/guides/contributing/">content pipeline guide</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
